"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code does not check if the data contains non-numeric values before applying the SimpleImputer with a 'mean' strategy. The 'mean' strategy can only be applied to numeric data.\",\n  \"patch\": \"11c11\\n<impt = SimpleImputer(missing_values=np.nan, strategy=\\\"mean\\\")\\n---\\n>impt = SimpleImputer(missing_values=np.nan, strategy=\\\"most_frequent\\\")\\n\\nAlternatively, you can select only numeric columns from the DataFrame before applying the SimpleImputer with 'mean' strategy:\\n\\n11c11\\n<impt = SimpleImputer(missing_values=np.nan, strategy=\\\"mean\\\")\\n12c12\\n<imp_array = impt.fit_transform(df)\\n---\\n>impt = SimpleImputer(missing_values=np.nan, strategy=\\\"mean\\\")\\n>imp_array = impt.fit_transform(df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]))\"\n}"